Sentencas: An active region of cathode interlayer in a tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is structurally analyzed using a dual-beam focused ion beam/scanning electron microscope (FIB/SEM).
Titulo: Pore orientation of the gadolinia-doped ceria cathode interlayer for a tubular SOFC using dip-coating

Sentencas: The GDC (10mol% gadolinia-doped ceria) cathode interlayer (about 1m in thickness) is dip-coated, and then sintered on YSZ (8mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia) electrolyte.
Titulo: Pore orientation of the gadolinia-doped ceria cathode interlayer for a tubular SOFC using dip-coating

Sentencas: At 1150 degrees C sintering temperature, the pores oriented more along the axial direction than the radial direction.
Titulo: Pore orientation of the gadolinia-doped ceria cathode interlayer for a tubular SOFC using dip-coating

Sentencas: The anisotropy of pore shape is accounted for the withdrawal force during the dip-coating of the GDC interlayer.
Titulo: Pore orientation of the gadolinia-doped ceria cathode interlayer for a tubular SOFC using dip-coating
